pullRequest.title: [risk=no] removing warnings about unchecked method invocation
pullRequest.bodyText:
workbench/api/src/main/java/org/pmiops/workbench/concept/ConceptService.java:171: warning: [unchecked] unchecked method invocation: method findConcepts in interface ConceptDao is applied to given types
? conceptDao.findConcepts(conceptTypes, domains, VOCAB_ID, CONCEPT_CLASS_ID, pageable)
^
required: ImmutableList,ImmutableList,String,String,Pageable
found: ImmutableList,ImmutableList,String,String,Pageable
/Users/jaycarlton/repos/workbench/api/src/main/java/org/pmiops/workbench/concept/ConceptService.java:171: warning: [unchecked] unchecked conversion
? conceptDao.findConcepts(conceptTypes, domains, VOCAB_ID, CONCEPT_CLASS_ID, pageable)

nodes.bodyText: nit: It's a bit difficult to read ternary statements where each branch is a method call with a bunch of parameters (and only one different). Rather than put the ternary operator in the return statement, I'd probably declare final matchExpression = StringUtils.isBlank(keyword) ? conceptTypes : keyword; Then you can return the same statement either way.
